Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of evolutionary robotics to construct a layered controller for a simulated robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves merging features from the subsumption architecture, which is a technique used in robotics and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks in the controller also falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the performance and evolvability of the approach, which could be considered machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY).
